    "It can be trained as similar to traditional SVM once the quantum kernel is obtained.",
    "In QSVM 43, the input data is transformed into quantum states |ϕ(x′) >.",
    "This can be achieved by performing quantum feature map v(ϕ(x')) in which ϕ is a classifier that can be applied to input data x'.",
    "Feature maps are done based on the Ansatz principle as given in Eq.",
    "(3) in which 'h n ' denotes the hadamard gate which is applied to each qubit and 'n' indicates several qubits."
